# frontend/ — Next.js web demo (TDD-07)

Voice + text demo UI (SkyGuide-style landing + dashboard) consuming the backend.
Design: `docs/tdd/TDD-07-Frontend.md`; usage: `frontend/README.md`.

## Run
```bash
cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev          # http://localhost:3000  (backend must be running)
npm run build        # production build
npm run typecheck    # tsc --noEmit  (keep this green)
```
Env: `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL` (default `http://127.0.0.1:8000`).

## Key conventions
- **Never call AirLabs (or any flight API) directly.** All flight data flows
  frontend → FastAPI → AirLabs; the key is server-side only.
- **The flight/ticket number is a typed input field**, validated — never relied on
  from audio (STT can't reliably extract codes). Voice is for natural questions.
- **Language is first-class:** the Language select drives the assistant's reply
  language (`en`/`fr`/`ary`); render assistant messages **RTL** for Arabic/Darija
  (`isRtl()` on the detected language).
- **Mic audio:** re-encode to **16 kHz mono WAV in-browser** before upload — the
  backend decoder can't read `MediaRecorder`'s webm/opus.
- The typed API client (`lib/*`) mirrors the backend contracts (TDD-06); if a
  contract changes, update the client AND `docs/tdd/TDD-07` (consistency rule).
- Keep the mic/`/converse` path — it demos the fine-tuned Whisper (the graded ML).
